Rating: 4
fetched rave reviews at a fourth of july party. i echo the sentiment of the other cook who said their topping bubbled over. either line the oven with some foil, use a higher sided dish, or go lighter on the fruit (last resort, as far as i'm concerned). very easy. best served the day it is baked, however, because the topping starts to lose its texture after resting overnight.

Rating: 4
Wonderful dish, I will make it every year. Everyone loved it, even my husband who doesn't like apricots. With so many apricots ripe at the same time it is difficult to use all of the fresh fruit. I think I will try freezing the filling in batches to use throughout the year.

Rating: 4
This was great! The people who ate it said it was the best cobbler EVER! I used blackberries and nectarines - 2 lbs. of each. The filling bubbled over a little when I baked it with the topping. So next time I will use a little less fruit. I did not use almond extract in the filling. I only mixed it with 1 cup of sugar and 3 tbl. of cornstarch. Dee-lish!

