I didn't think this is worth making again. The topping must have soaked up all the juices because the filling was dry. I did add the lemon zest to the topping which gave it a nice flavor. Maybe less cornstarch is needed.

Rating: 3
Frozen cherries and canned apricots work fine in this recipe. A couple of comments: I found the fruit filling a little too sweet, and suggest adding only 1/2-2/3 C to the fruit mixture. Also, the topping is a bit plain. Adding 1.5 T lemon zest makes it more flavourful.

Rating: 3
I made this today with cherries (frozen) and peaches instead of apricots (those being nowhere in sight) Two things I would change...I think it needs a bit less almond extract, and I also think less topping. With #2 cherries and #2 peaches, the topping "ate" a lot of the fruit syrup. If I make it again, I will make 1/2 the topping.

Rating: 3
Very nice. As suggested by a previous reviewer, I used peaches and blueberries. I like a lot of fruit, but don't use much more than 7 or 8 cups of fruit total. Even though more fruit will "fit" in a 13" x 9" pan, it will bubble over and spill (and burn on the bottom of the oven), so don't get overly enthusiastic with the fruit (ah, the voice of experience... said as I am STILL cleaning the oven from this...). The biscuit topping is very nice and delicate -- I sprinkled cinnamon sugar over the "crust" before baking, which was also nice.

